originalText.text: I was the manager in Jefferson Houses for 8 years and worked diligently with the residents and community to improve the quality of life. I engaged with many wonderful, hardworking and concerned residents. East Harlem has improved considerably and I liked my experiences there with the loving people of Harlem. It was a difficult job but I achieved satisfaction and achievement there. Crime had decreased there due to the police impact program for 5 years. I must warn any future manager that this development is not an 8:30-4:30pm job. I can't recall how many times I left work @ 4:30 daily. This included some of my Housing Assistants also. There is never ending paperwork to be done there. I am now retired and wish the new Manager and staff much success which can undoubtedly be accomplished. Work hard and be attentive to your resident leaders and residents in general because they really care. Miss my seniors who comprise a large population there.
